cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  The first Asking Bid we're going to look at is Beta.

This is a "general" control-asking bid and is potentially available in most bidding sequences, not just ones where Asking Bids have already been established.

Beta is the Precision equivalent of Blackwood, since it asks how many Aces and Kings partner has in their hand.

Beta is the ONLY Asking bid of this type (ie: one that doesn't have to be part of an Asking Bid sequence, and which doesn't kick off an Asking Bid sequence Generally speaking, the following bids can be Beta: 

^c|cp|r|at|^*b[1]  High-level Beta: ^*n|cp||at|   In natural auctions if a suit OTHER THAN clubs have been agreed, or if Clubs have not been suggested as trumps, then 4@C can be Beta (but see below).

^c|cp|r|at|^*b[2]  High-level Beta: ^*n|cp||at|   If Clubs HAVE been agreed as trumps in a natural sequence, then 4@D can be Beta (but see below).

Next I will show you a hand that we will keep returning to

