^*bRedbird44:^*n  Is the question I need to ask as responder?  -  'Have I limited my hand'  -  so I can tell in advance if my bid will be Beta or a cue-bid?

|cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|   Well if you HAVE limited your hand, and partner has NOT, then generally you should be leaving it up to them to make the running in slam investigation.  This is, however, a fairly fluid thing.

The above doesn't mean that a player who HAS limited their hand cannot, for example, initiate cue-bidding if partner seems to be strong but generally using Beta is NORMALLY (not always) left up to the stronger hand.

An exception to this is in  2@D  sequences where the bidding might start   2@D - 2@H - 2@S - 2NT - 3@D(@H shortage).

But although Opener has shown a strong hand, and it's now open to the notionally weaker hand to use Beta in @H.

Essentially we're following what I said above: 

Responder here is completely unlimited (but may have nothing), and Opener HAS now limited their hand by virtue of the  2@S  bid.

