cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|   A few other points about Beta: 

(1) ^cIn  @2some sequences you can have a SECOND Beta Ask during the same sequence, when the answer to a Low-level Beta got a 0-2 Controls response.

The SECOND Beta will automatically be on the Weak scale in these circumstances.

We never need a third Beta Ask in ANY sequence.


^b(2)^cAs stated earlier, a 1, 2, 3 or 4 - step response to Alpha will ALWAYS affect the Scale in any subsequent Beta (ie: If 1 or 3 steps in response to Alpha, any later Beta will use the Weak Scale, and if 2 or 4 steps in response to Alpha, any later Beta will use the Strong Scale).


^b(3)^cBeta is not ALWAYS the best route to find out what you need to know.

Bear this in mind if, for example, you have a void somewhere and there is, perhaps, one specific suit where you need partner to have their Controls.   Here perhaps better to ignore Beta and use Epsilon instead.


^b(4)^cTry to improve your ANALYSIS skills.

Quite often a degree of concentrated analysis of the hand will tell you a lot about what partner has, their distribution and where their controls are.

This will help you to target your Asking Bids most effectively.|
